  <summary>3/20/2002--Introduced.
National Integrative Center for Homeland Security Act of 2002 - Requires the Director of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, together with a U.S. college or university, to establish and operate a National Integrative Center for Homeland Security to provide a coordinated, science-based approach to enhance the Nation's homeland security. Sets forth criteria for the Director to consider in selecting the college or university.</summary>
